	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Learners residing in Waterloo House at Wynberg Girls' High School in Cape Town are picketing outside the school.The learners earlier in the week sent out a statement with allegations of ill treatment by the house mother.Some learners who have finished writing their exam are picketing outside while waiting on their friends to finish their exams.Learners say they have received an email from the school stating that they will be arrested if they take part in the picket.Some members of UCT's student representative council (SRC) have joined the picketing learners.Click here to watch a video of the picket.Some parents fetched their children from school early following news of the planned picket.The police are also on the scene.More to follow.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  